I'm Alastair Budge, and today we are going to be talking about When Britain Killed Its King.

00:00:29.734 --> 00:00:35.534
On January 30th, 1649, outside the Palace of Whitehall, in

00:00:35.534 --> 00:00:40.864
central London, a man walked up to a large, raised stage.

00:00:41.414 --> 00:00:46.914
Below him, thousands of people waited eagerly to see history made.

00:00:47.894 --> 00:00:52.514
The man knelt on the ground, and made a signal with his hand.

00:00:53.184 --> 00:00:59.964
On this signal, a man whose face was covered raised an axe high and brought

00:01:00.034 --> 00:01:05.054
